sense.name: [provide with a new or different resting place
sense.examples: Lyou Ye then reseated herself behind her desk and frowned. Djuro reseated himself, sipping cautiously at his own glass. Once we were all reseated, he went to the front of the room. Jaime reseated the ball cap covering his thick shock of hair. The usher insisted on reseating us. They need to be reseated inside, now. Move them from our table and reseat them!
